snippet: The strong jobs report and a rise in interest rates helped lift the indexes, and raised questions about what the data would mean for the Federal Reserve’s stimulus program.
abstract: Unexpectedly strong jobs report gives stocks lift, pushing Dow Jones industrial average to another high.
lead_paragraph: The strong jobs report and a rise in interest rates helped lift the indexes, and raised questions about what the data would mean for the Federal Reserve’s stimulus program.

headline.main: Jobs Report Elevates Dow to a New High
